<collectingCountry box="[359,426,1485,1511]" name="Israel" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Israel</collectingCountry>
: Hermon Mountain.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,656,1655]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1521,1547]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is named after the collector of the 
<typeStatus box="[903,951,1521,1547]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">type</typeStatus>
series, Dr. Amnon Freidberg, a well-known Israeli dipterist and enthusiastic collector of insects all over the world, curator of insect collection during many years in the Steinhardt Museum of Natural History, 
<collectingCountry box="[681,743,1593,1619]" name="Israel" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Israel</collectingCountry>
National Center for Biodiversity Studies and Department of Zoology, 
<collectingRegion box="[258,353,1629,1655]" country="Israel" name="Tel Aviv" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Tel Aviv</collectingRegion>
University.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
